# `+1.5` is invalid syntax in cgpipe — there is no unary `+` operator. The
# tokenizer emits a binary `+` with no left side, which the evaluator now
# rejects cleanly with a "Operator '+' has no left operand" error rather than
# crashing with a Java stack trace.
#
# test.sh normalizes "CGPIPE ERROR.*" to just "CGPIPE ERROR" before MD5, so
# the .good file just pins the prefix.

print +1.5
